turn false;\\n        }\\n\\n        public String getName()\\n        {\\n            return \\\"Anonymous\\\";\\n        }\\n\\n        public boolean authenticate(Object credentials)\\n        {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n    }\\n\\n    /* ------------------------------------------------------------ */\\n    /* ------------------------------------------------------------ */\\n    /* ------------------------------------------------------------ */\\n    public static class KnownUser implements UserPrincipal,Serializable\\n    {\\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = -6226920753748399662L;\\n        private final String _name;\\n        private final Credential _credential;\\n\\n        /* -------------------------------------------------------- */\\n        public KnownUser(String name,Credential credential)\\n        {\\n            _name=name;\\n            _credential=credential;\\n        }\\n\\n        /* -------------------------------------------------------- */\\n        public boolean authenticate(Object credentials)\\n        {\\n            return _credential!=null && _credential.check(credentials);\\n        }\\n\\n        /* ------------------------------------------------------------ */\\n        public String getName()\\n        {\\n            return _name;\\n        }\\n\\n        /* -------------------------------------------------------- */\\n        public boolean isAuthenticated()\\n        {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        /* -------------------------------------------------------- */\\n        @Override\\n        public String toString()\\n        {\\n            return _name;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777737000996}]}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-security:9.3.19.v20170502/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-52-51-875947Z.log:1128:[thinking] I’m thinking about using Class.forName to obtain an observable connection. I'm considering whether to use a dynamic proxy for the connection. But could I just return null to avoid issues? If Driver.connect doesn't accept the URL, it will return null, and DriverManager will move on without throwing a suitable SQLException. I wonder if I can assert that there won’t be a throw. The connectDatabase method will catch SQL exceptions, and maybe I should use a static Atomic count to track connection attempts.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-security:9.3.19.v20170502/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-52-51-875947Z.log:1142:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating database connection options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using Class.forName to obtain an observable connection. I'm considering whether to use a dynamic proxy for the connection. But could I just return null to avoid issues? If Driver.connect doesn't accept the URL, it will return null, and DriverManager will move on without throwing a suitable SQLException. I wonder if I can assert that there won’t be a throw. The connectDatabase method will catch SQL exceptions, and maybe I should use a static Atomic count to track connection attempts.\\n\\n**Evaluating static initialization**\\n\\nI'm considering what happens during static initialization when accessing a reset. Reset indeed triggers initialization and registers, which leads to the doStart method in the public constructor. But if the DriverManager retains the driver across tests, it seems like it only pertains to one test. I think deregistration happens finally, but if another use comes after deregistration, it won't work. So, must ensure to call TestDriver.deregister() effectively.\\n\\n**Considering test code structure**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether test code can be modern with Java 17; it seems fine to 