,\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating static initialization**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering what happens during static initialization when accessing a reset. Reset indeed triggers initialization and registers, which leads to the doStart method in the public constructor. But if the DriverManager retains the driver across tests, it seems like it only pertains to one test. I think deregistration happens finally, but if another use comes after deregistration, it won't work. So, must ensure to call TestDriver.deregister() effectively.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering test code structure**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about whether test code can be modern with Java 17; it seems fine to me. I want to ensure I check the style guidelines like Checkstyle, and I know a public class is necessary. Also, I'm wondering if using lowercase with underscores for the package name would be acceptable. I need to remember to include a license too, and maybe the user-code-filter should allow the test package. Let's read through that.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_9cKhJBpEBGfrxBmDcVprx87u|fc_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d3f37648194a8cd1fd480c45444\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-security/9.3.19.v20170502/user-code-filter.json\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2562, \"output\": 1334, \"cacheRead\": 11776, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 15672, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777737001008, \"responseId\": \"resp_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d295a808194a9e80110f8024402\"}}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-security:9.3.19.v20170502/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-52-51-875947Z.log:1155:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_9cKhJBpEBGfrxBmDcVprx87u|fc_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d3f37648194a8cd1fd480c45444\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\n  \\\"rules\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"excludeClasses\\\": \\\"**\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"includeClasses\\\": \\\"org.eclipse.jetty.security.**\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777737023567}}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-security:9.3.19.v20170502/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-52-51-875947Z.log:1156:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_9cKhJBpEBGfrxBmDcVprx87u|fc_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d3f37648194a8cd1fd480c45444\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\n  \\\"rules\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"excludeClasses\\\": \\\"**\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"includeClasses\\\": \\\"org.eclipse.jetty.security.**\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777737023567}}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-security:9.3.19.v20170502/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-52-51-875947Z.log:1157:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating database connection options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using Class.forName to obtain an observable connection. I'm considering whether to use a dynamic proxy for the connection. But could I just return null to avoid issues? If Driver.connect doesn't accept the URL, it will return null, and DriverManager will move on without throwing a suitable SQLException. I wonder if I can assert that there won’t be a throw. The connectDatabase method will catch SQL exceptions, and maybe I should use a static Atomic count to track connection attempts.\\n\\n**Evaluating static initialization**\\n\\nI'm considering what happens during static initialization when accessing a reset. Reset indeed triggers initialization and registers, which leads to the doStart method in the public constructor. But if the DriverManager retains the driver across tests, it seems like it only pertains to one test. I think deregistration happens finally, but if another use comes after deregistration, it won't work. So, must ensure to call TestDriver.deregister() effectively.\\n\\n**Considering test code structure**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether test code can be modern with Java 17; it seems fine to me. I want to ensure I check the style guidelines like Checkstyle, and I know a public class is necessary. Also, I'm wondering if using lowercase with underscores for the package name would be acceptable. I need to remember to include a license too, and maybe the user-code-filter should allow the test package. Let's read through that.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d29d32881948705424a833e7b35\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9h0_qY1bnRg6JxJ2NuJw8ElX24fWR_QV8AAZ4WkZ6CV3xIoYtOspRdfy5UAE9HDxRYqWWTsRaBJWuh9DcRsj5Uv6zgw6kL2suTRXHISOGAUQxLQiHQ2Tve8tI3v0bqCSazEgOsijsFqm4YiXdUa8Ah0yft9c7Br35UFoMDfP1Yuhvt_jb5s4swibeV0-vcTYOt6dDlSkrFCd4W_3-BgD1ISgU-SInYnOFp8wv73uEN2Ve-tjYk5FrW00537RuRlVgV94OL9iT26x6EKYOrvnT2v5Z4CVfOFOIoePLzrEu0PNH3i-WaQZFuivcC6sHt4d17IcMnumvz9oo_dRVCLHSoYH5rDW4EKHRCjYLxZGQ3JykYcSOVmo7GabLCeEkFtQpjsG3IAC0H_BV3VUMLEI7fmMPZuf7oay5Rl26go-Q9spj3iDTPd3JYniWZ_Lrp0udn7ao4Gqlpp_CcbSvVs1YKcRBZGp16uzHG4WV6YdDEWcoWKxESEE2zqc2N_9rr9ZFAFikGLAquJ5sIKUUBHFqrR0dai2C57tI8RfUty8G1G9mk6Wi6V35dASxmFYQsMV6ESyLOyE0nRm5PkZVkjQ9BZsI_MqSUjjrZnQdQDPi-znJ-bQ70z0-48PP8j2HHe8mYmF9d9ogX8tk2pF9YuaAgyFmkjfkdJc_jfRFdO-3k6b-yj-nmcb98DRXgT206oKTi3i7KR3U1ljYXtnZvxj4yuIHGK1lL-hXX4l6S1HhAduyoESX4htaDqqsqUCIaBLPiVcOQJy1iD9tf9BTExzLpFq0fccsG4lFXSG1iC-bORL577P5iU4eu3mCEPcNgdTHbpk5NnzgK4ZbmDDK98xxU2CGj8Httot-fY_oM1