eads our connection to return null as well. However, there's an odd case where it returns null even when acceptsURL is true. The JDBC spec suggests a connection should be returned if the URL is accepted, but maybe that’s not a strict requirement. The plot thickens with SQLException being caught for no suitable driver.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating checkstyle for tests**\\\\n\\\\nI need to check the checkstyle configuration for tests. It seems important to ensure that the code adheres to the style guidelines we want to follow, especially when it comes to tests. I'll take a look at the current checkstyle settings and see if there are any adjustments needed to make everything consistent. Having a good configuration is key to maintaining code quality. Let's dive in and sort this out!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_y9C09Niw0WCB753B430W7Y50|fc_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d6383d0819482ba8ba0dda42089\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find . -iname '*checkstyle*' -type f | sort | head -20 && rg \\\"EmptyBlock|Unused\\\" -n config gradle build.gradle settings.gradle . | head -50\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1399, \"output\": 821, \"cacheRead\": 18432, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 20652, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777737046384, \"responseId\": \"resp_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d56de808194b1a08dc91d1ef661\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_y9C09Niw0WCB753B430W7Y50|fc_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d6383d0819482ba8ba0dda42089\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"./.github/workflows/checkstyle.yml\\n./gradle/checkstyle.xml\\n./tests/tck-build-logic/build/classes/groovy/main/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/CheckstyleInvocationTask