nitialization and registers, which leads to the doStart method in the public constructor. But if the DriverManager retains the driver across tests, it seems like it only pertains to one test. I think deregistration happens finally, but if another use comes after deregistration, it won't work. So, must ensure to call TestDriver.deregister() effectively.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Considering test code structure**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI'm thinking about whether test code can be modern with Java 17; it seems fine to me. I want to ensure I check the style guidelines like Checkstyle, and I know a public class is necessary. Also, I'm wondering if using lowercase with underscores for the package name would be acceptable. I need to remember to include a license too, and maybe the user-code-filter should allow the test package. Let's read through that.\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_9cKhJBpEBGfrxBmDcVprx87u|fc_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d3f37648194a8cd1fd480c45444\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"read\\\", \\\"arguments\\\": {\\\"path\\\": \\\"tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-security/9.3.19.v20170502/user-code-filter.json\\\"}}], \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-responses\\\", \\\"provider\\\": \\\"OCA\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 2562, \\\"output\\\": 1334, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 11776, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"totalTokens\\\": 15672, \\\"cost\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 0, \\\"output\\\": 0, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 0, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"total\\\": 0}}, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"toolUse\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": 1777737001008, \\\"responseId\\\": \\\"resp_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d295a808194a9e80110f8024402\\\"}, \\\"toolResults\\\": [{\\\"role\\\": \\\"toolResult\\\", \\\"toolCallId\\\": \\\"call_9cKhJBpEBGfrxBmDcVprx87u|fc_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d3f37648194a8cd1fd480c45444\\\", \\\"toolName\\\": \\\"read\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"rules\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    {\\\\n      \\\\\\\"excludeClasses\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"**\\\\\\\"\\\\n    },\\\\n    {\\\\n      \\\\\\\"includeClasses\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"org.eclipse.jetty.security.**\\\\\\\"\\\\n    }\\\\n  ]\\\\n}\\\\n\\\"}], \\\"isError\\\": false, \\\"timestamp\\\": 1777737023567}]}\\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-security:9.3.19.v20170502/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-52-51-875947Z.log:1163:[tool-call] delta {\\\"path\\\":\\\"tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-security/9.3.19.v20170502/src/test/java/org_eclipse_jetty/jetty_security/JDBCLoginServiceTest.java\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"/*\\\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\\\n *\\\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\\\n */\\\\npackage org_eclipse_jetty.jetty_security;\\\\n\\\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\\\n\\\\nimport java.io.IOException;\\\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\\\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\\\\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\\\\nimport java.sql.Driver;\\\\nimport java.sql.DriverManager;\\\\nimport java.sql.DriverPropertyInfo;\\\\nimport java.sql.SQLException;\\\\nimport java.util.Properties;\\\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\\\\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\\\\n\\\\nimport org.eclipse.jetty.security.JDBCLoginService;\\\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\\\\n\\\\npublic class JDBCLoginServiceTest {\\\\n    @TempDir\\\\n    Path tempDir;\\\\n\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void startsWithConfiguredJdbcDriverAndAttemptsConnection() throws Exception {\\\\n        TestDriver.resetCounters();\\\\n        Path configFile = writeJdbcRealmProperties();\\\\n        JDBCLoginService loginService = new JDBCLoginService(\\\\\\\"jdbc-test\\\\\\\", configFile.toUri().toString